+# Verification Report — T-009@20260416T043834Z
+
+**Verify Agent:** Codex
+**Date:** 2026-04-16
+**Artifacts Reviewed:** [my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py), [my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py), [tests/test_resource_governor.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/tests/test_resource_governor.py), [my-claw/tools/daemon.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/daemon.py), [my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py), [my-claw/tools/first_boot.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/first_boot.py), [tests/test_first_boot.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/tests/test_first_boot.py), [ESCALATIONS.md](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/ESCALATIONS.md), [git log --oneline -5](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw), [git diff HEAD~3 --stat](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw), [git diff HEAD~3](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw)
+
+## Correctness
+
+CPU, node count, sampler load, capture freshness, self-listener RMS, and master-bus health are all read and combined into a pressure score in `resource_governor.py`, and tests cover these combinations.
+
+However, the integration in `duet_composer.py` only applies `max_voices`, `allow_color`, and `allow_counter` to the cast before generation. The computed `grain_density`, `density_multiplier`, `suppress_llm`, and `dsp_blocks_allowed` are not used. This means optional sample/grain and primary-form degradation is not enforced in actual rendering yet, so “degrades optional voices/samples/grains before interrupting primary form” is only partially implemented.
+
+Identity bootstrap hardening remains incomplete for startup surfaces that still execute `cypherclaw_daemon.py`: that file sends the startup banner and proceeds without `bootstrap_identity()`, so first-run identity creation is not guaranteed in that runtime path.
+
+## Completeness
+
+The new unit suite (`test_resource_governor.py`) is comprehensive and catches the requested pressure scenarios, and full `pytest tests/ -x` passes (2119 passed).
+
+Gaps remain:
+- Degradation knobs computed by `ResourceBudget` are not exercised in the composer output path.
+- No end-to-end or integration test currently proves governor-driven cast/synthesis fallback under live pressure in `tracker_solo_song` (unit tests only).
+- Startup identity wiring is only verified in the daemon startup path covered by `daemon.py` in this commit set, while `cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()`.
+
+## Consistency
+
+- `resource_governor.py` follows a clean, stdlib-only design and test naming is consistent with repository style.
+- The feature is wired into existing composition path via imports and a budget reason print block, but only partially consumes the budget contract, which is inconsistent with the stated intent of `ResourceBudget` fields.
+- The `FirstBootAnnouncer`/`bootstrap_identity` flow is currently split/inconsistent between startup files.
+
+## Security
+
+No secrets or unsafe command execution are introduced by this task.
+
+A residual risk is still operational: skipping bootstrap in one startup path can leave missing identity files and force implicit reinitialization behavior if downstream code depends on identity persistence.
+
+## Quality
+
+`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x` ran successfully in this environment.
+
+- Result: `2119 passed`
+- Warnings: only deprecation warnings and existing environment noise; no task-related test failures.
+
+The implementation quality is good in core computation and test coverage for the new governor module, but deployment completeness and runtime enforcement are incomplete.
+
+## Issues Found
+- [ ] Incomplete budget enforcement: budget fields for grain density, global density multiplier, LLM suppression, and DSP budget are computed but never applied in `tracker_solo_song`, so sample/grain and primary-form fallback is not actually enforced (`my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`). Severity: blocking.
+- [ ] Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking.
+- [ ] Missing mandatory regression: no startup integration test in this task verifies identity persistence across boots through `bootstrap_identity()` within both startup execution paths (`my-claw/tools/daemon.py` and `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`). Existing tests validate bootstrap helpers but not the complete runtime wiring from launch entrypoint. Severity: minor.
+
+## Verdict: FAIL
+
+## Notes for Lead Agent
+
+1. Apply `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` startup flow, mirroring the `daemon.py` path.
+2. Thread `ResourceBudget.grain_density`, `density_multiplier`, `suppress_llm`, and `dsp_blocks_allowed` into `tracker_solo_song` (and any alternate generation path) before rendering, with explicit fallbacks to prune optional samples/grains and cap primary density before more disruptive cuts.
+3. Add one or two integration tests that execute startup + first boot for both entrypoints and assert identity persistence across restart, and add a governor-to-composition integration test that confirms audible output still succeeds under healthy conditions and degrades gracefully under high pressure (`pytest`-driven, no subprocess-heavy mocking).
